</h3><ul style="--pf-line-spacing-xs:10px;--pf-line-spacing-sm:10px;--pf-line-spacing-md:10px;--pf-line-spacing-lg:10px;--pf-text-indent-xs:0px;--pf-text-indent-sm:0px;--pf-text-indent-md:0px;--pf-text-indent-lg:0px" data-pf-type="List2" class="sc-bQtKYq czWvgn pf-34_"><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-35_ pf-text-1"><strong>Qualification </strong>- A certification that a learner has achieved a specific level of knowledge, skills, and understanding in a particular subject or vocational area.




</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-37_ pf-text-1"><strong>Awarding body</strong> - An organisation that develops, assesses, and awards qualifications. Examples include AQA, OCR, and Pearson.








</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-39_ pf-text-1"><strong>Regulation </strong>- The process of setting and enforcing standards to ensure consistency, reliability, and fairness in qualifications and assessments.









